  "prompt": "How can I record video with Drift Ghost-S while charging?",
  "response": "To record video with the Drift Ghost-S while charging, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Charge the Camera**: Before starting, ensure your Drift Ghost-S is charged using the provided USB cable. Connect it to a power source such as a wall adapter, power bank, or any USB power supply.\n\n2. **Set Up for Recording**: Turn on the Drift Ghost-S and adjust your settings for video recording, such as resolution and frame rate, according to your preference.\n\n3. **Connect the Power Supply**: If you want to charge the camera while recording, connect the USB cable from the Drift Ghost-S to a power bank or any other USB power source. Make sure that the power source is capable of providing sufficient power for both charging and operation.\n\n4. **Start Recording**: Once everything is properly connected, you can press the record button to start capturing video. The camera should continue to function while being powered.\n\n5. **Monitor Battery and Heat**: Keep an eye on the battery status indicator and monitor the camera for any excessive heat during prolonged usage. Continuous recording while charging can sometimes cause the camera to heat up.\n\n6. **Use a Suitable Mount**: If you're using the camera outdoors or while in motion (e.g., on a motorcycle or bike), ensure that it is securely mounted and that the power cable doesn\u2019t interfere with your activities.\n\nRemember to check the user manual of the Drift Ghost-S for any specific instructions or warnings about charging and recording simultaneously. This will ensure a smooth operation and help avoid any potential damage to the camera.",
